content.text:
I have constructed a highly elegant, responsive, and collaborative Kanban board for the team. It is fully aligned with Robert Murdock's Polaris/Workspace Design System (WDS) and utilizes standard Google Workspace colors, real team member assignees with their actual avatars, and the native flat-file state synchronization API to support real-time cooperative updates.

The board tracks the specific tasks from your Project Sojo workspace, including initial tasks mapped directly from the "Business in a Box" meeting notes and the "Task as a primitive in Sojo" product brief.

### Key Highlights
- **Real-Time Synchronizer Support:** Implements short-polling every 2 seconds via `POST/GET /api/sync/:envId/:key` to coordinate board updates in real-time.
- **WDS Design Fidelity:** Adheres to the exact WDS spacing variables, Google Sans typography, Material Design 3 (M3) flat-color containers, and high-quality minimal aesthetics.
- **Absolute Scope Discipline:** Contains three clean columns (`To Do`, `In Progress`, `Done`) without distracting, unrequested clutter (such as priority badges, due dates, filters, or complex popups).
- **Interactive UI:** Users can easily transfer tasks between stages with simple click controls, delete tasks, or dynamically add new tasks.

